Brazil. Spatial dynamic models were conceived to simulate past land
cover/land use changes (2005-2010) and future landscape scenarios
(2010-2020) in the study area. The main observed changes that took place
from 2005 to 2010 were: sugarcane expansion (6,012.71ha (49.68\%)),
mostly extending over grazing lands, and deforestation (3,107.16ha
