The availability of wide-ranging building inventory data allowed the application of a GIS-based loss estimation model (KoeriLoss-V2) to evaluate different loss scenarios depending on the ground shaking input, as well as to consider the implications of mitigation actions. It was found that 30\% of the buildings in the metropolitan area may be in need of either strengthening or demolition to achieve an adequate degree of life safety. (c) 2008 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.},
